record.title: EXPRESSING THE SENSE OF THE SENATE THAT ATTORNEY GENERAL ALBERTO GONZALES NO LONGER HOLDS THE CONFIDENCE OF THE SENATE AND OF THE AMERICAN PEOPLE--MOTION TO PROCEED

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I move to proceed to S.J. Res. 14 and send a cloture motion to the desk.

record.chair: The cloture motion having been presented under rule XXII, the Chair directs the clerk to read the motion.

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I withdraw my motion to proceed.
